<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/1986a:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-17T15:00:00-04:00">November 17, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1225. For your information, Helsinki reports that Finnish press
                                “accurately representing Finnish people” is united in denunciation
                                of terms of unconditional surrender for Finland and “resolve to
                                fight on to the end”, rather than accept such terms.<note n="42" xml:id="d226fn42">The BBC’s broadcast of November 15, 1943, had
                                    quoted the Soviet Red Army newspaper, <hi rend="italic">Krasnaya
                                        Zvezda</hi>, to the effect that Finland must surrender
                                    unconditionally.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>